item.dc:creator: @hidendra Hidendra
item.description:
@hidendra wrote:

Sorry, but I’m going to put this plainly: if you can do the so-called 503 you’ve done yourself, then why didn’t you see this? Even if you never got the error before, that’s not a reason to say you didn’t read the code.

i = anInt1211 - 112; - aClass9_1059.anInt224;

You have a semi-colon then a dash[minus] sign. That, obviously, is not a statement. Remove the semi-colon. If you followed a tutorial, it was possibly “anti-leech”.
